Notes from Arnaud: Longevity. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Instantaneous growth rate at small size. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Maximum size. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Theoretical age of zero length. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Constant of proportionality of the allometric length-weight relationship. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Exponent of the allometric length-weight relationship. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Size at sexual maturity. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Age at sexual maturity. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind. Please have a look at jhpoelen/fb-osmose-bridge#15
Threshold age below which a linear growth model is used to calculate mean length increase. This is a parameter that could easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind

Length-weight relationship estimated for total lengths (TLs)?: Boolean variable. This is a parameter that I created for the OSMOSE-WFS model but which will undoubtedly be useful for other OSMOSE applications. This parameter could easily be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind
Annual number of eggs per gram of mature female. This is a parameter that could easily be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind
Female:male sex ratio. This is a parameter that could easily be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind
